# Agent Server Design: Unified Multi-Agent Abstraction

## Research Summary

Analyzed three codebases to inform the design:

1. **Our Sidecar** (current) — JSON-RPC over Unix socket, `AgentHandler` interface with Claude + Codex implementations
2. **Codex App Server** (OpenAI) — Rust JSON-RPC server with rich thread/turn/item lifecycle, approval system, and generated TypeScript protocol types
3. **OpenDevs** — Effect-based provider adapter pattern with orchestration engine, CQRS event sourcing, and WebSocket transport

---

## Comparison: What Each App Does

### Domain Model

| Concept | Our Sidecar | Codex App Server | OpenDevs |
|---------|-------------|------------------|---------|
| Conversation unit | `session` | `thread` | `thread` (within orchestration) |
| Message round | implicit (query/response) | `turn` | `turn` |
| Streaming unit | raw SDK message | `item` (typed: agentMessage, commandExecution, fileChange, etc.) | `ProviderRuntimeEvent` with canonical item types |
| Agent identity | `agentType: "claude" \| "codex"` | single provider (OpenAI) | `ProviderKind` (currently `"codex"` only) |
| Session state | in-memory Map | server-managed thread lifecycle | orchestration read model + provider session |

### Protocol Methods (Client → Server)

| Method | Our Sidecar | Codex App Server | OpenDevs |
|--------|-------------|------------------|---------|
| Initialize | — | `initialize` | WS connection + `server.welcome` |
| Start session | implicit (first `query`) | `thread/start` | `thread.create` + `thread.turn.start` |
| Send message | `query` | `turn/start` | `thread.turn.start` |
| Steer/redirect | — | `turn/steer` | — |
| Cancel/interrupt | `cancel` | `turn/interrupt` | `thread.turn.interrupt` |
| Resume | `query` with `resume` option | `thread/resume` | `thread.turn.start` with `resumeCursor` |
| Approve tool | — (handled by SDK) | `execCommandApproval`, `applyPatchApproval`, `item/commandExecution/requestApproval`, `item/fileChange/requestApproval` | `thread.approval.respond` |
| User input | — (handled by SDK) | `item/tool/requestUserInput` | `thread.user-input.respond` |
| List threads | — | `thread/list`, `thread/loaded/list` | `orchestration.getSnapshot` |
| Read thread | — | `thread/read` | `orchestration.getSnapshot` |
| Archive/delete | — | `thread/archive`, `thread/unarchive` | `thread.delete` |
| Fork thread | — | `thread/fork` | — |
| Rollback | — | `thread/rollback` | `thread.checkpoint.revert` |
| Rename | — | `thread/name/set` | `thread.meta.update` |
| Auth | `claudeAuth` | `getAuthStatus`, `account/login/start` | — |
| Models | — | `model/list` | — |
| MCP servers | `workspaceInit` | `mcpServerStatus/list` | — |
| Context usage | `contextUsage` | — | — |
| Permission mode | `updatePermissionMode` | — | `thread.runtime-mode.set` |
| Config | — | `config/read`, `config/value/write` | `server.getConfig` |
| Reset generator | `resetGenerator` | — | — |
| Compact context | — | `thread/compact/start` | — |

### Server → Client Events

| Event | Our Sidecar | Codex App Server | OpenDevs |
|-------|-------------|------------------|---------|
| Message delta | `message` notification | `item/agentMessage/delta` | `thread.message.assistant.delta` |
| Item started | — | `item/started` | activity append |
| Item completed | — | `item/completed` | `thread.message.assistant.complete` |
| Turn started | — | `turn/started` | `thread.turn-start-requested` event |
| Turn completed | `statusChanged` | `turn/completed` | orchestration event |
| Thread status | `statusChanged` | `thread/status/changed` | orchestration event |
| Error | `queryError` | `error` notification | orchestration event |
| Plan mode | `enterPlanModeNotification` | `item/plan/delta` | `thread.proposed-plan.upsert` |
| Diff updated | — | `turn/diff/updated` | `thread.turn-diff-completed` |
| Reasoning | — | `item/reasoning/textDelta`, `item/reasoning/summaryTextDelta` | — |
| Token usage | — | `thread/tokenUsage/updated` | — |
| Command output | — | `item/commandExecution/outputDelta` | activity append |
| File change output | — | `item/fileChange/outputDelta` | activity append |

---

## Proposed Design: Unified Agent Server

### Core Abstractions (Thread + Turn + Item model, inspired by Codex)

```typescript
// ── Domain Types ─────────────────────────────────────────────────

type AgentType = "claude" | "codex" | "gemini" | "custom";

type ThreadStatus = "idle" | "working" | "waiting_for_approval" | "error" | "archived";
type TurnStatus = "running" | "completed" | "failed" | "interrupted" | "cancelled";
type ItemType =
  | "agent_message" | "user_message" | "reasoning"
  | "command_execution" | "file_change" | "mcp_tool_call"
  | "web_search" | "plan" | "context_compaction" | "error";

interface Thread {
  id: ThreadId;
  agentType: AgentType;
  workspaceId: string;
  status: ThreadStatus;
  title: string | null;
  model: string;
  cwd: string;
  createdAt: string;
  updatedAt: string;
  // Resume support
  agentSessionId: string | null;  // SDK-specific session/thread ID
}

interface Turn {
  id: TurnId;
  threadId: ThreadId;
  status: TurnStatus;
  startedAt: string;
  completedAt: string | null;
  error: TurnError | null;
}

interface ThreadItem {
  id: ItemId;
  threadId: ThreadId;
  turnId: TurnId;
  type: ItemType;
  // Discriminated payload per type
  content: ItemContent;
  startedAt: string;
  completedAt: string | null;
}
```

### Agent Adapter Interface

Drawing from all three:

```typescript
interface AgentAdapterCapabilities {
  /** Can check auth status */
  auth: boolean;
  /** Can list MCP servers and slash commands */
  workspaceInit: boolean;
  /** Can report context window usage */
  contextUsage: boolean;
  /** Supports changing model mid-session without restart */
  modelHotSwap: boolean;
  /** Supports changing permission/approval mode mid-session */
  permissionModeSwitch: boolean;
  /** Supports multi-turn within a single generator/connection */
  multiTurn: boolean;
  /** Supports forking/branching conversation history */
  threadFork: boolean;
  /** Supports rolling back N turns */
  threadRollback: boolean;
  /** Supports context compaction */
  contextCompaction: boolean;
  /** Supports approval/rejection of tool calls from outside */
  externalApproval: boolean;
  /** Supports structured user input requests */
  userInputRequests: boolean;
}

interface AgentAdapter {
  readonly agentType: AgentType;
  readonly capabilities: AgentAdapterCapabilities;

  // ── Lifecycle ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

  /** One-time setup: verify binaries, load config */
  initialize(): Promise<InitializeResult>;

  /** Clean shutdown: kill processes, release resources */
  shutdown(): Promise<void>;

  // ── Thread Management ──────────────────────────────────────────

  /** Start a new agent thread/session */
  startThread(params: ThreadStartParams): Promise<Thread>;

  /** Resume an existing thread (from disk/DB or agent session ID) */
  resumeThread(params: ThreadResumeParams): Promise<Thread>;

  /** Stop/close a thread's backing agent session */
  stopThread(threadId: ThreadId): Promise<void>;

  // ── Turn Execution ─────────────────────────────────────────────

  /**
   * Send a user message and start a new turn.
   * Returns immediately with turn metadata; streaming happens via events.
   */
  startTurn(params: TurnStartParams): Promise<TurnStartResult>;

  /**
   * Interrupt/cancel a running turn.
   */
  interruptTurn(threadId: ThreadId, turnId: TurnId): Promise<void>;

  /**
   * Steer: inject a follow-up message into a running turn
   * (multi-turn generators like Claude support this).
   */
  steerTurn?(params: TurnSteerParams): Promise<void>;

  // ── Approval / User Input ──────────────────────────────────────

  /**
   * Respond to a tool approval request from the agent.
   */
  respondToApproval?(params: ApprovalResponseParams): Promise<void>;

  /**
   * Respond to a structured user input request.
   */
  respondToUserInput?(params: UserInputResponseParams): Promise<void>;

  // ── Configuration Hot-Swap ─────────────────────────────────────

  /** Change model on active session (if capability allows) */
  setModel?(threadId: ThreadId, model: string): Promise<void>;

  /** Change permission/approval mode */
  setPermissionMode?(threadId: ThreadId, mode: PermissionMode): Promise<void>;

  // ── Queries ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  /** Check auth/account status */
  getAuthStatus?(params: AuthParams): Promise<AuthStatus>;

  /** Get MCP servers + slash commands available in workspace */
  getWorkspaceCapabilities?(params: WorkspaceInitParams): Promise<WorkspaceCapabilities>;

  /** Get context window usage for a thread */
  getContextUsage?(threadId: ThreadId): Promise<ContextUsage>;

  /** List available models for this agent type */
  listModels?(): Promise<ModelInfo[]>;

  // ── Event Stream ───────────────────────────────────────────────

  /**
   * Canonical event stream emitted by this adapter.
   * All adapters normalize their native events into AgentEvent.
   */
  readonly events: AsyncIterable<AgentEvent>;
}
```

### Parameter Types

```typescript
interface ThreadStartParams {
  threadId: ThreadId;
  workspaceId: string;
  agentType: AgentType;
  model?: string;
  cwd: string;
  permissionMode?: PermissionMode;
  // Agent-specific env/config
  env?: Record<string, string>;
  additionalDirectories?: string[];
  sandboxMode?: SandboxMode;
}

interface ThreadResumeParams {
  threadId: ThreadId;
  agentSessionId?: string;  // SDK-specific resume token
  model?: string;
  cwd?: string;
  permissionMode?: PermissionMode;
}

interface TurnStartParams {
  threadId: ThreadId;
  input: UserInput[];        // text, images, mentions, skills
  model?: string;            // override for this turn
  interactionMode?: "default" | "plan";
}

interface TurnSteerParams {
  threadId: ThreadId;
  turnId: TurnId;
  input: UserInput[];
}

type UserInput =
  | { type: "text"; text: string }
  | { type: "image"; url: string }
  | { type: "localImage"; path: string }
  | { type: "mention"; name: string; path: string };

type PermissionMode =
  | "default"
  | "acceptEdits"
  | "bypassPermissions"
  | "plan"
  | "dontAsk";

type SandboxMode =
  | "read-only"
  | "workspace-write"
  | "full-access";

interface ApprovalResponseParams {
  threadId: ThreadId;
  requestId: string;
  decision: "accept" | "acceptForSession" | "decline" | "cancel";
}

interface UserInputResponseParams {
  threadId: ThreadId;
  requestId: string;
  answers: Record<string, unknown>;
}

interface TurnStartResult {
  threadId: ThreadId;
  turnId: TurnId;
  accepted: boolean;
  reason?: string;
}
```

### Event Types (Adapter → Server → Frontend)

```typescript
type AgentEvent =
  // Thread lifecycle
  | { type: "thread.started"; thread: Thread }
  | { type: "thread.status_changed"; threadId: ThreadId; status: ThreadStatus }
  | { type: "thread.closed"; threadId: ThreadId }

  // Turn lifecycle
  | { type: "turn.started"; threadId: ThreadId; turn: Turn }
  | { type: "turn.completed"; threadId: ThreadId; turn: Turn }

  // Item streaming
  | { type: "item.started"; threadId: ThreadId; turnId: TurnId; item: ThreadItem }
  | { type: "item.delta"; threadId: ThreadId; turnId: TurnId; itemId: ItemId; delta: string }
  | { type: "item.completed"; threadId: ThreadId; turnId: TurnId; item: ThreadItem }

  // Approval requests (server → frontend)
  | { type: "approval.requested"; threadId: ThreadId; request: ApprovalRequest }
  | { type: "approval.resolved"; threadId: ThreadId; requestId: string }

  // User input requests
  | { type: "user_input.requested"; threadId: ThreadId; request: UserInputRequest }
  | { type: "user_input.resolved"; threadId: ThreadId; requestId: string }

  // Metadata
  | { type: "context.compacted"; threadId: ThreadId }
  | { type: "token_usage.updated"; threadId: ThreadId; usage: TokenUsage }
  | { type: "model.rerouted"; threadId: ThreadId; from: string; to: string }

  // Errors
  | { type: "error"; threadId: ThreadId; error: AgentError };

interface ApprovalRequest {
  requestId: string;
  kind: "command_execution" | "file_change" | "file_read" | "apply_patch";
  params: Record<string, unknown>;  // command, path, patch, etc.
}

interface UserInputRequest {
  requestId: string;
  questions: Array<{
    id: string;
    prompt: string;
    required: boolean;
    schema?: unknown;  // JSON Schema for validation
  }>;
}

interface AgentError {
  message: string;
  category: "auth" | "rate_limit" | "context_limit" | "network"
          | "abort" | "invalid_request" | "process_exit" | "internal";
}
```

### Adapter Registry

```typescript
class AgentAdapterRegistry {
  private adapters = new Map<AgentType, AgentAdapter>();

  register(adapter: AgentAdapter): void;
  get(agentType: AgentType): AgentAdapter | undefined;

  /** Initialize all registered adapters, return failures */
  initializeAll(): Promise<Map<AgentType, InitializeResult>>;

  /** Shut down all adapters */
  shutdownAll(): Promise<void>;

  /** Merged event stream from all adapters */
  get events(): AsyncIterable<AgentEvent>;

  /** Get capabilities for a specific agent type */
  getCapabilities(agentType: AgentType): AgentAdapterCapabilities | undefined;
}
```

---

## Key Design Decisions

### 1. Thread/Turn/Item Model (from Codex)
The Codex app-server's `thread → turn → item` hierarchy is the right abstraction. It cleanly separates:
- **Thread** = persistent conversation context (our current "session")
- **Turn** = one user→agent round trip (currently implicit in our `query`)
- **Item** = typed streaming unit within a turn (currently opaque SDK messages)

### 2. Adapter Pattern (from OpenDevs)
OpenDevs's `ProviderAdapter` → `ProviderService` layering is excellent:
- **Adapter** = provider-specific (knows Claude SDK, Codex SDK internals)
- **Service** = provider-agnostic facade that routes by thread → adapter
- Clean separation lets us add new agents without touching the routing layer

### 3. External Approval System (from Codex)
Both Codex and OpenDevs externalize tool approval:
- Agent requests approval → server emits `approval.requested` event → frontend shows UI → user decides → server sends decision back to agent
- This is a must-have for our product — we currently delegate this entirely to the SDK's internal approval flow

### 4. Event-Driven (from OpenDevs's CQRS)
OpenDevs's CQRS pattern with `OrchestrationCommand` → `OrchestrationEvent` is powerful:
- Commands are inputs (user actions)
- Events are outputs (state changes)
- The read model (snapshot) is derived from events
- We don't need full event sourcing, but the command/event separation maps cleanly to our WS protocol

### 5. Capabilities Declaration (enhanced from ours)
Our current `AgentCapabilities { auth, workspaceInit, contextUsage, permissionMode }` is good but too narrow. The expanded set above covers all the features we'd want to progressively support per agent.

---

## Migration Path from Current Architecture

| Current | New | Change |
|---------|-----|--------|
| `AgentHandler.query()` | `AgentAdapter.startTurn()` + `AgentAdapter.steerTurn()` | Split fire-and-forget query into explicit turn start + multi-turn steer |
| `AgentHandler.cancel()` | `AgentAdapter.interruptTurn()` | Add turnId parameter for precision |
| `AgentHandler.reset()` | `AgentAdapter.stopThread()` | Rename + thread-scoped |
| `AgentHandler.initialize()` | `AgentAdapter.initialize()` | Same |
| `SessionState` in-memory maps | `Thread` + `Turn` DB-backed | Persist turn history for rollback/fork |
| `FrontendClient.sendMessage()` | `AgentEvent` stream | Decouple adapter from transport |
| `saveUserMessage()` in sidecar | Move to server layer | Adapter shouldn't do DB writes |
| `protocol.ts` Zod schemas | Shared typed event schemas | Same approach, expanded event types |

---

## What's NOT In Scope (Yet)

- **Sub-agents / multi-agent orchestration** (Codex has `collabAgentToolCall`, T3 has multi-thread orchestration) — defer until core adapter pattern is solid
- **Checkpointing / git integration** (T3 has per-turn git checkpoints) — we have diff stats already
- **Plugin/skill management** (Codex has `plugin/*`, `skills/*`) — separate concern
- **Voice/realtime** (Codex has `thread/realtime/*`) — not relevant to coding agents

