  1→# Agent Server Design: Unified Multi-Agent Abstraction
  2→
  3→## Research Summary
  4→
  5→Analyzed three codebases to inform the design:
  6→
  7→1. **Our Sidecar** (current) — JSON-RPC over Unix socket, `AgentHandler` interface with Claude + Codex implementations
  8→2. **Codex App Server** (OpenAI) — Rust JSON-RPC server with rich thread/turn/item lifecycle, approval system, and generated TypeScript protocol types
  9→3. **OpenDevs** — Effect-based provider adapter pattern with orchestration engine, CQRS event sourcing, and WebSocket transport
 10→
 11→---
 12→
 13→## Comparison: What Each App Does
 14→
 15→### Domain Model
 16→
 17→| Concept | Our Sidecar | Codex App Server | OpenDevs |
 18→|---------|-------------|------------------|---------|
 19→| Conversation unit | `session` | `thread` | `thread` (within orchestration) |
 20→| Message round | implicit (query/response) | `turn` | `turn` |
 21→| Streaming unit | raw SDK message | `item` (typed: agentMessage, commandExecution, fileChange, etc.) | `ProviderRuntimeEvent` with canonical item types |
 22→| Agent identity | `agentType: "claude" \| "codex"` | single provider (OpenAI) | `ProviderKind` (currently `"codex"` only) |
 23→| Session state | in-memory Map | server-managed thread lifecycle | orchestration read model + provider session |
 24→
 25→### Protocol Methods (Client → Server)
 26→
 27→| Method | Our Sidecar | Codex App Server | OpenDevs |
 28→|--------|-------------|------------------|---------|
 29→| Initialize | — | `initialize` | WS connection + `server.welcome` |
 30→| Start session | implicit (first `query`) | `thread/start` | `thread.create` + `thread.turn.start` |
 31→| Send message | `query` | `turn/start` | `thread.turn.start` |
 32→| Steer/redirect | — | `turn/steer` | — |
 33→| Cancel/interrupt | `cancel` | `turn/interrupt` | `thread.turn.interrupt` |
 34→| Resume | `query` with `resume` option | `thread/resume` | `thread.turn.start` with `resumeCursor` |
 35→| Approve tool | — (handled by SDK) | `execCommandApproval`, `applyPatchApproval`, `item/commandExecution/requestApproval`, `item/fileChange/requestApproval` | `thread.approval.respond` |
 36→| User input | — (handled by SDK) | `item/tool/requestUserInput` | `thread.user-input.respond` |
 37→| List threads | — | `thread/list`, `thread/loaded/list` | `orchestration.getSnapshot` |
 38→| Read thread | — | `thread/read` | `orchestration.getSnapshot` |
 39→| Archive/delete | — | `thread/archive`, `thread/unarchive` | `thread.delete` |
 40→| Fork thread | — | `thread/fork` | — |
 41→| Rollback | — | `thread/rollback` | `thread.checkpoint.revert` |
 42→| Rename | — | `thread/name/set` | `thread.meta.update` |
 43→| Auth | `claudeAuth` | `getAuthStatus`, `account/login/start` | — |
 44→| Models | — | `model/list` | — |
 45→| MCP servers | `workspaceInit` | `mcpServerStatus/list` | — |
 46→| Context usage | `contextUsage` | — | — |
 47→| Permission mode | `updatePermissionMode` | — | `thread.runtime-mode.set` |
 48→| Config | — | `config/read`, `config/value/write` | `server.getConfig` |
 49→| Reset generator | `resetGenerator` | — | — |
 50→| Compact context | — | `thread/compact/start` | — |
 51→
 52→### Server → Client Events
 53→
 54→| Event | Our Sidecar | Codex App Server | OpenDevs |
 55→|-------|-------------|------------------|---------|
 56→| Message delta | `message` notification | `item/agentMessage/delta` | `thread.message.assistant.delta` |
 57→| Item started | — | `item/started` | activity append |
 58→| Item completed | — | `item/completed` | `thread.message.assistant.complete` |
 59→| Turn started | — | `turn/started` | `thread.turn-start-requested` event |
 60→| Turn completed | `statusChanged` | `turn/completed` | orchestration event |
 61→| Thread status | `statusChanged` | `thread/status/changed` | orchestration event |
 62→| Error | `queryError` | `error` notification | orchestration event |
 63→| Plan mode | `enterPlanModeNotification` | `item/plan/delta` | `thread.proposed-plan.upsert` |
 64→| Diff updated | — | `turn/diff/updated` | `thread.turn-diff-completed` |
 65→| Reasoning | — | `item/reasoning/textDelta`, `item/reasoning/summaryTextDelta` | — |
 66→| Token usage | — | `thread/tokenUsage/updated` | — |
 67→| Command output | — | `item/commandExecution/outputDelta` | activity append |
 68→| File change output | — | `item/fileChange/outputDelta` | activity append |
 69→
 70→---
 71→
 72→## Proposed Design: Unified Agent Server
 73→
 74→### Core Abstractions (Thread + Turn + Item model, inspired by Codex)
 75→
 76→```typescript
 77→// ── Domain Types ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
 78→
 79→type AgentType = "claude" | "codex" | "gemini" | "custom";
 80→
 81→type ThreadStatus = "idle" | "working" | "waiting_for_approval" | "error" | "archived";
 82→type TurnStatus = "running" | "completed" | "failed" | "interrupted" | "cancelled";
 83→type ItemType =
 84→  | "agent_message" | "user_message" | "reasoning"
 85→  | "command_execution" | "file_change" | "mcp_tool_call"
 86→  | "web_search" | "plan" | "context_compaction" | "error";
 87→
 88→interface Thread {
 89→  id: ThreadId;
 90→  agentType: AgentType;
 91→  workspaceId: string;
 92→  status: ThreadStatus;
 93→  title: string | null;
 94→  model: string;
 95→  cwd: string;
 96→  createdAt: string;
 97→  updatedAt: string;
 98→  // Resume support
 99→  agentSessionId: string | null;  // SDK-specific session/thread ID
100→}
101→
102→interface Turn {
103→  id: TurnId;
104→  threadId: ThreadId;
105→  status: TurnStatus;
106→  startedAt: string;
107→  completedAt: string | null;
108→  error: TurnError | null;
109→}
110→
111→interface ThreadItem {
112→  id: ItemId;
113→  threadId: ThreadId;
114→  turnId: TurnId;
115→  type: ItemType;
116→  // Discriminated payload per type
117→  content: ItemContent;
118→  startedAt: string;
119→  completedAt: string | null;
120→}
121→```
122→
123→### Agent Adapter Interface
124→
125→Drawing from all three:
126→
127→```typescript
128→interface AgentAdapterCapabilities {
129→  /** Can check auth status */
130→  auth: boolean;
131→  /** Can list MCP servers and slash commands */
132→  workspaceInit: boolean;
133→  /** Can report context window usage */
134→  contextUsage: boolean;
135→  /** Supports changing model mid-session without restart */
136→  modelHotSwap: boolean;
137→  /** Supports changing permission/approval mode mid-session */
138→  permissionModeSwitch: boolean;
139→  /** Supports multi-turn within a single generator/connection */
140→  multiTurn: boolean;
141→  /** Supports forking/branching conversation history */
142→  threadFork: boolean;
143→  /** Supports rolling back N turns */
144→  threadRollback: boolean;
145→  /** Supports context compaction */
146→  contextCompaction: boolean;
147→  /** Supports approval/rejection of tool calls from outside */
148→  externalApproval: boolean;
149→  /** Supports structured user input requests */
150→  userInputRequests: boolean;
151→}
152→
153→interface AgentAdapter {
154→  readonly agentType: AgentType;
155→  readonly capabilities: AgentAdapterCapabilities;
156→
157→  // ── Lifecycle ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
158→
159→  /** One-time setup: verify binaries, load config */
160→  initialize(): Promise<InitializeResult>;
161→
162→  /** Clean shutdown: kill processes, release resources */
163→  shutdown(): Promise<void>;
164→
165→  // ── Thread Management ──────────────────────────────────────────
166→
167→  /** Start a new agent thread/session */
168→  startThread(params: ThreadStartParams): Promise<Thread>;
169→
170→  /** Resume an existing thread (from disk/DB or agent session ID) */
171→  resumeThread(params: ThreadResumeParams): Promise<Thread>;
172→
173→  /** Stop/close a thread's backing agent session */
174→  stopThread(threadId: ThreadId): Promise<void>;
175→
176→  // ── Turn Execution ─────────────────────────────────────────────
177→
178→  /**
179→   * Send a user message and start a new turn.
180→   * Returns immediately with turn metadata; streaming happens via events.
181→   */
182→  startTurn(params: TurnStartParams): Promise<TurnStartResult>;
183→
184→  /**
185→   * Interrupt/cancel a running turn.
186→   */
187→  interruptTurn(threadId: ThreadId, turnId: TurnId): Promise<void>;
188→
189→  /**
190→   * Steer: inject a follow-up message into a running turn
191→   * (multi-turn generators like Claude support this).
192→   */
193→  steerTurn?(params: TurnSteerParams): Promise<void>;
194→
195→  // ── Approval / User Input ──────────────────────────────────────
196→
197→  /**
198→   * Respond to a tool approval request from the agent.
199→   */
200→  respondToApproval?(params: ApprovalResponseParams): Promise<void>;
201→
202→  /**
203→   * Respond to a structured user input request.
204→   */
205→  respondToUserInput?(params: UserInputResponseParams): Promise<void>;
206→
207→  // ── Configuration Hot-Swap ─────────────────────────────────────
208→
209→  /** Change model on active session (if capability allows) */
210→  setModel?(threadId: ThreadId, model: string): Promise<void>;
211→
212→  /** Change permission/approval mode */
213→  setPermissionMode?(threadId: ThreadId, mode: PermissionMode): Promise<void>;
214→
215→  // ── Queries ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
216→
217→  /** Check auth/account status */
218→  getAuthStatus?(params: AuthParams): Promise<AuthStatus>;
219→
220→  /** Get MCP servers + slash commands available in workspace */
221→  getWorkspaceCapabilities?(params: WorkspaceInitParams): Promise<WorkspaceCapabilities>;
222→
223→  /** Get context window usage for a thread */
224→  getContextUsage?(threadId: ThreadId): Promise<ContextUsage>;
225→
226→  /** List available models for this agent type */
227→  listModels?(): Promise<ModelInfo[]>;
228→
229→  // ── Event Stream ───────────────────────────────────────────────
230→
231→  /**
232→   * Canonical event stream emitted by this adapter.
233→   * All adapters normalize their native events into AgentEvent.
234→   */
235→  readonly events: AsyncIterable<AgentEvent>;
236→}
237→```
238→
239→### Parameter Types
240→
241→```typescript
242→interface ThreadStartParams {
243→  threadId: ThreadId;
244→  workspaceId: string;
245→  agentType: AgentType;
246→  model?: string;
247→  cwd: string;
248→  permissionMode?: PermissionMode;
249→  // Agent-specific env/config
250→  env?: Record<string, string>;
251→  additionalDirectories?: string[];
252→  sandboxMode?: SandboxMode;
253→}
254→
255→interface ThreadResumeParams {
256→  threadId: ThreadId;
