414→
415→### 4. Event-Driven (from OpenDevs's CQRS)
416→OpenDevs's CQRS pattern with `OrchestrationCommand` → `OrchestrationEvent` is powerful:
417→- Commands are inputs (user actions)
418→- Events are outputs (state changes)
419→- The read model (snapshot) is derived from events
420→- We don't need full event sourcing, but the command/event separation maps cleanly to our WS protocol
421→
422→### 5. Capabilities Declaration (enhanced from ours)
423→Our current `AgentCapabilities { auth, workspaceInit, contextUsage, permissionMode }` is good but too narrow. The expanded set above covers all the features we'd want to progressively support per agent.
