428→
429→| Current | New | Change |
430→|---------|-----|--------|
431→| `AgentHandler.query()` | `AgentAdapter.startTurn()` + `AgentAdapter.steerTurn()` | Split fire-and-forget query into explicit turn start + multi-turn steer |
432→| `AgentHandler.cancel()` | `AgentAdapter.interruptTurn()` | Add turnId parameter for precision |
433→| `AgentHandler.reset()` | `AgentAdapter.stopThread()` | Rename + thread-scoped |
434→| `AgentHandler.initialize()` | `AgentAdapter.initialize()` | Same |
435→| `SessionState` in-memory maps | `Thread` + `Turn` DB-backed | Persist turn history for rollback/fork |
436→| `FrontendClient.sendMessage()` | `AgentEvent` stream | Decouple adapter from transport |
437→| `saveUserMessage()` in sidecar | Move to server layer | Adapter shouldn't do DB writes |
438→| `protocol.ts` Zod schemas | Shared typed event schemas | Same approach, expanded event types |
439→
440→---
441→
442→## What's NOT In Scope (Yet)
443→
444→- **Sub-agents / multi-agent orchestration** (Codex has `collabAgentToolCall`, T3 has multi-thread orchestration) — defer until core adapter pattern is solid
445→- **Checkpointing / git integration** (T3 has per-turn git checkpoints) — we have diff stats already
446→- **Plugin/skill management** (Codex has `plugin/*`, `skills/*`) — separate concern
447→- **Voice/realtime** (Codex has `thread/realtime/*`) — not relevant to coding agents
