# Agent Server Design: Unified Multi-Agent Abstraction

## Research Summary

Analyzed four codebases to inform the design:

1. **Our Sidecar** (current) — JSON-RPC over Unix socket, `AgentHandler` interface with Claude + Codex implementations
2. **Codex App Server** (OpenAI) — Rust JSON-RPC server with rich thread/turn/item lifecycle, approval system, and generated TypeScript protocol types
3. **OpenDevs** — Effect-based provider adapter pattern with orchestration engine, CQRS event sourcing, and WebSocket transport
4. **Agnt (our cloud)** — Cloudflare Workers + Durable Objects + E2B sandboxes, with raw SDK event passthrough, transform pipeline adapter pattern, and external permission/hook bridge

---

## Comparison: What Each App Does

### Domain Model

| Concept | Our Sidecar | Codex App Server | OpenDevs | Agnt (Cloud) |
|---------|-------------|------------------|---------|--------------|
| Conversation unit | `session` | `thread` | `thread` (orchestration) | `session` (Durable Object) |
| Message round | implicit (query/response) | `turn` | `turn` | `turn` (turnId in message) |
| Streaming unit | raw SDK message | `item` (typed) | `ProviderRuntimeEvent` | `Part` (TEXT, REASONING, TOOL, STEP_FINISH) |
| Agent identity | `agentType: "claude" \| "codex"` | single provider (OpenAI) | `ProviderKind` (`"codex"`) | `agentType: "claude-code" \| "codex"` |
| Session state | in-memory Map | server-managed thread | orchestration read model | DO SQLite + Postgres sync |
| Event transform | per-agent in handler | native Rust | canonical runtime events | `Adapter<TEvent>` + `EventTransformer` pipeline |
| Sandbox | — | built-in (macOS sandbox) | — | E2B cloud VMs |

### Protocol Methods (Client → Server)

| Method | Our Sidecar | Codex App Server | OpenDevs | Agnt (Cloud) |
|--------|-------------|------------------|---------|--------------|
| Initialize | — | `initialize` | WS connection + `server.welcome` | DO `initialize()` RPC |
| Start session | implicit (first `query`) | `thread/start` | `thread.create` + `thread.turn.start` | `postMessage()` (auto-creates turn) |
| Send message | `query` | `turn/start` | `thread.turn.start` | `message.send` (client WS command) |
| Steer/redirect | — | `turn/steer` | — | — (generator reuse via AsyncQueue) |
| Cancel/interrupt | `cancel` | `turn/interrupt` | `thread.turn.interrupt` | `agent.cancel` (client WS command) |
| Resume | `query` with `resume` option | `thread/resume` | `thread.turn.start` with `resumeCursor` | auto-resume via `agentSessionId` |
| Approve tool | — (handled by SDK) | `execCommandApproval`, `applyPatchApproval` | `thread.approval.respond` | `permission.response` (client WS) |
| User input | — (handled by SDK) | `item/tool/requestUserInput` | `thread.user-input.respond` | `mcp.answer` (client WS) |
| Hook response | — | — | — | `hook.response` (client WS) |
| List threads | — | `thread/list` | `orchestration.getSnapshot` | — |
| Archive/delete | — | `thread/archive` | `thread.delete` | — |
| Fork thread | — | `thread/fork` | — | — |
| Rollback | — | `thread/rollback` | `thread.checkpoint.revert` | — |
| Auth | `claudeAuth` | `getAuthStatus` | — | — (API key in execute options) |
| Permission mode | `updatePermissionMode` | — | `thread.runtime-mode.set` | in execute options |
| Reset generator | `resetGenerator` | — | — | `shouldResetGenerator` option |

### Server → Client Events

| Event | Our Sidecar | Codex App Server | OpenDevs | Agnt (Cloud) |
|-------|-------------|------------------|---------|--------------|
| Message delta | `message` notification | `item/agentMessage/delta` | `thread.message.assistant.delta` | `message.part` (typed Part) |
| Item started | — | `item/started` | activity append | Part with `STREAMING` state |
| Item completed | — | `item/completed` | `thread.message.assistant.complete` | Part with `DONE` state |
| Turn started | — | `turn/started` | `thread.turn-start-requested` | `turn.started` |
| Turn completed | `statusChanged` | `turn/completed` | orchestration event | `turn.ended` (with usage/cost) |
| Message completed | — | — | — | `message.ended` (with usage/cost) |
| Thread status | `statusChanged` | `thread/status/changed` | orchestration event | `agent:status` → DO state change |
| Error | `queryError` | `error` notification | orchestration event | `agent:status` failed |
| Permission request | — | `requestApproval` | orchestration event | `permission.request` |
| MCP question | — | — | — | `mcp.question` |
| Hook event | — | — | — | `hook.request` / `hook.event` |
| Context compaction | — | — | — | `session.compacting` |
| Reasoning | — | `item/reasoning/textDelta` | — | REASONING Part |
| Token usage | — | `thread/tokenUsage/updated` | — | in `turn.ended` payload |

---

## Proposed Design: Unified Agent Server

### Core Abstractions (Thread + Turn + Item model, inspired by Codex)

```typescript
// ── Domain Types ─────────────────────────────────────────────────

type AgentType = "claude" | "codex" | "gemini" | "custom";

type ThreadStatus = "idle" | "working" | "waiting_for_approval" | "error" | "archived";
type TurnStatus = "running" | "completed" | "failed" | "interrupted" | "cancelled";
type ItemType =
